done America,” he said. “Just look at the traffic. The city has changed enormously. I was here, you know, in ‘twenty-four.”

“I was living in Prague at the time,” said Lev.

“I see,” said Serafim.

Silence. They both watched the teapot, as if they expected some miracle from it.

“It’s going to boil soon,” said Lev. “Have some of these caramels in the meantime.”

Serafim did and his left cheek started working. Lev still could not bring himself to sit down: sitting meant 